description.narrative: As a result of high-level advocacy and;UNICEF;support for;the government’s;evidence generation;and decision-making process, the;Maldives;Bureau;of Statistics officially launched the;country’s first ever;National Multidimensional;Vulnerability;Index (MVI),;built;on the national;Multidimensional Poverty Index (MPI).;The MVI maps vulnerability across;the;country,;highlighting;concentrations;of vulnerable populations,;providing;solid evidence;for;programme;targeting;and;possible reallocation of;resources.;To further strengthen the evidence-based decision-making process,;UNICEF is supporting;government to compile;comprehensive information on disability by including;six;core;questions;on disability in the upcoming;2022;census.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/01/2022
